rComments: All lectures are asynchronous and recycled from the previous year. Complicated topics are covered in minimal detail. Synchronous online content only involves doing practice questions; participation is mandatory. No one in the class really understands how to answer his practice questions. It is awkward and uncomfortable. Avoid.
By far the worse professor I have ever had. His condescending attitude towards students shows how little he really cares.
Really felt like he didnt care. Agree with previous commenters that his expectations are completely unclear. Would not recommend.

I had this professor for a French Online Course. Easily the worst class I took in my third year of law school. The prof is not clear on his expectations for the students and didn't answer questions adequately. The teacher didn't seem to care about his students/class. If possible, take the mandatory administrative law course with another prof.
Awful professor.  Snooty attitude.  Went through 65-70 slides each class, couldnt answer questions and completely unclear about expectations for his students.
